rComments: Has English Second Language Accent, so isn't perfectly clear when he talks during lecture.

so far THE BEST math professor I've had at U of T. He is so down to earth and cares a lot about his students. He is always willing to help his students both in class and after class. He even had a review session before the final. Love him sooo much! sad that he will not be teaching anymore....

One of the friendliest and jolliest instructors I've ever had. Always in a good mood. He cares a lot for his students. Goes over lots of examples similar to test questions, tells you what to expect on tests, easy quizzes in tutorial, explains well and proves things in class. Rarely puts proofs on test. Sad to hear he isn't teaching anymore.

Great professor. He managed keep me interested in the class while also making it fun. He is also funny which makes for a better learning environment. He went above and beyond the syllabus by teaching really hard problems that weren't on the tests. However, learning those problems made it easier to learn the ones that were on the tests.
